al interactions affect women's achievement in math and science in particular this research tests how interpersonal cues that create a sense of working with others rather than against others can allay concerns about negative stereotypes and thus improve women's performance in otherwise psychologically threatening conditions read more location serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 fellow's lunch featuring corey fields date & time thursday may 17 2012 11 45am to 1 00pm description corey field assistant professor in the department of sociology studies race identity and culture for his fellowship fields will explore how race mediates perceptions about why women are single the clayman institute faculty research fellows lunch seminars are aimed at faculty all faculty are welcome to attend please rsvp to andrea davies ardavies stanford edu if you wish to attend read more location serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 donate make a donation social links facebook twitter youtube scribd contact serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 map 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu
